HEADWORD: Air gap
<hw>Air gap</hw>. <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>An air-filled gap in a
magnetic or electric circuit; specif., in a dynamo or motor, the space
between the field-magnet poles and the armature; clearance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Air gas</ent>⟦br⟧
